<name>threshold</name>
<qualifiedname>ndigo6g12_trigger::threshold</qualifiedname>
<briefdescription>
<para>Threshold controlling when the ADC channel is active. </para>
</briefdescription>
<detaileddescription>
<para>Sets the threshold for the trigger block within the range of the ADC data. The range depends on <ref refid="structndigo6g12__configuration_1aaf241640a83ec470bf6c337d6426ae33" kindref="member">ndigo6g12_configuration::output_mode</ref>:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__outputdefs_1gabb1307aecd252b329c43d44ea8f0e3da" kindref="member">NDIGO6G12_OUTPUT_MODE_RAW</ref> : 0 to 4096</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="group__outputdefs_1ga47484f82a72759a22685cb14a6b8e457" kindref="member">NDIGO6G12_OUTPUT_MODE_SIGNED16</ref> : &#8722;32768 to 32767</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
For trigger indices <ref refid="group__triggerdefs" kindref="compound">NDIGO6G12_TRIGGER_TDC </ref> to <ref refid="group__triggerdefs" kindref="compound">NDIGO6G12_TRIGGER_ONE </ref> the threshold is ignored.</para>
<para>For the TDC channels, the trigger threshold is controlled by <ref refid="structndigo6g12__configuration_1aa6bf60e4eaac106ccf3902c1a8f5d942" kindref="member">ndigo6g12_configuration::tdc_trigger_offsets</ref>. </para>
</detaileddescription>
